we really don\'t need the [anki](https://apps.ankiweb.net/) when we have `emacs` and `org-mode`

## Setting up Org-Drill

in your `doom-emacs` configuration files `config.el` add the following function

``` elisp
(defun my/org-drill-by-tags (tags-match)
  "Run org-drill on entries in the zettelkasten matching TAGS-MATCH.
TAGS-MATCH is an org tags match string like '+claude_code+_fact' or '+claude_code'."
  (interactive "sTags match (e.g. +claude_code+_fact): ")
  (let ((drill-dirs '("/home/savolla/resource/notes/org/roam/zettels"
                      "/home/savolla/resource/notes/org/roam/biblio/notes"
                      "/home/savolla/resource/notes/org/roam/journal"))
        (entries '()))
    (dolist (dir drill-dirs)
      (dolist (file (directory-files-recursively dir "\\.org$"))
        (with-current-buffer (find-file-noselect file)
          (org-map-entries
           (lambda ()
             (when (member "drill" (org-get-tags))
               (push (point-marker) entries)))
           tags-match
           'file))))
    (if entries
        (org-drill-entries entries)
      (message "No drill entries found matching: %s" tags-match))))
```

